statements: SELECT * FROM email_engagement WHERE id = '12345678-1234-5678-1234-567812345678';
SELECT * FROM email_engagement WHERE engagement_time > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM email_engagement WHERE sender_email = 'example@test.com' AND engagement_type = 'open';
SELECT sender_email, engagement_time FROM email_engagement ORDER BY engagement_time DESC;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_engagements, engagement_type FROM email_engagement GROUP BY engagement_type;
SELECT id, sender_email, recipient_email, engagement_time, engagement_type FROM email_engagement WHERE sender_email = 'john.doe@example.com' ORDER BY engagement_time DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT id, sender_email, engagement_type FROM email_engagement WHERE recipient_email = 'jane.smith@example.com' ORDER BY engagement_time ASC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM email_engagement WHERE engagement_type = 'open' ORDER BY engagement_time DESC, sender_email ASC LIMIT 5;
SELECT id, engagement_type FROM email_engagement WHERE engagement_time > '2022-01-01' AND engagement_time < '2022-12-31' ORDER BY sender_email ASC, engagement_time ASC LIMIT 3;
SELECT DISTINCT sender_email FROM email_engagement WHERE engagement_type = 'click' ORDER BY sender_email DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM users
SELECT email, registration_date FROM users
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM users ORDER BY engagement_score DESC
SELECT * FROM email_logs WHERE open_status = true
SELECT user_id, send_date, open_status FROM email_logs ORDER BY send_date
SELECT * FROM users WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT email, registration_date FROM users WHERE engagement_score > 50 ORDER BY registration_date DESC;
SELECT user_id, COUNT(log_id) AS email_count FROM email_logs GROUP BY user_id HAVING email_count > 3 ORDER BY user_id;
SELECT users.user_id, users.email, email_logs.send_date FROM users INNER JOIN email_logs ON users.user_id = email_logs.user_id WHERE email_logs.open_status = true;
SELECT user_id, AVG(engagement_score) AS avg_score FROM users GROUP BY user_id HAVING avg_score > 40 ORDER BY user_id DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM users;
SELECT user_id, email_address FROM users WHERE first_name = 'John';
SELECT user_id, first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE registration_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM email_logs ORDER BY sent_date DESC;
SELECT engagement_type, engagement_date FROM email_engagement WHERE user_id = 12345 AND engagement_type = 'click';
SELECT * FROM users WHERE email_address = 'example@gmail.com';
SELECT first_name, last_name FROM users WHERE registration_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT user_id, email_address FROM users ORDER BY user_id DESC;
SELECT email_logs.user_id, email_engagement.engagement_type FROM email_logs JOIN email_engagement ON email_logs.email_id = email_engagement.email_id;
SELECT u.first_name, e.engagement_date FROM users u JOIN email_engagement e ON u.user_id = e.user_id;
SELECT * FROM users;
SELECT email, username FROM users ORDER BY created_at DESC;
SELECT subject, body FROM emails WHERE sent_at > '2022-01-01';
SELECT email_id, opened_at FROM opens WHERE user_id = 123 ORDER BY opened_at ASC;
SELECT click_id, clicked_at FROM clicks WHERE email_id = 456 AND user_id = 789;
SELECT * FROM users WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT email, username FROM users WHERE created_at < '2022-01-01';

SELECT users.username, emails.subject, opens.opened_at FROM users INNER JOIN emails ON users.user_id = emails.user_id INNER JOIN opens ON emails.email_id = opens.email_id WHERE users.username LIKE 'A%';

SELECT users.username, emails.subject, clicks.clicked_at FROM users INNER JOIN emails ON users.user_id = emails.user_id INNER JOIN clicks ON emails.email_id = clicks.email_id WHERE users.username <> 'admin';

SELECT users.username, emails.subject, opens.opened_at, clicks.clicked_at FROM users INNER JOIN emails ON users.user_id = emails.user_id LEFT JOIN opens ON emails.email_id = opens.email_id LEFT JOIN clicks ON emails.email_id = clicks.email_id WHERE users.user_id IN (1, 2, 3);
SELECT * FROM EmailSubscribers;
SELECT email_address, subscription_date FROM EmailSubscribers ORDER BY subscription_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM EmailCampaigns WHERE total_recipients > 100;
SELECT campaign_name, start_date, end_date FROM EmailCampaigns WHERE total_recipients < 50 ORDER BY start_date ASC;
SELECT email_id, subscriber_id, click_date FROM EmailClicks WHERE click_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-03-31';
SELECT * FROM EmailSubscribers ORDER BY engagement_score DESC, subscription_date ASC
SELECT subscriber_id, email_address, engagement_score FROM EmailSubscribers WHERE subscription_date > '2022-01-01' AND engagement_score > 50 ORDER BY engagement_score DESC
SELECT e.campaign_name, COUNT(ec.email_id) AS total_clicks FROM EmailCampaigns e JOIN EmailClicks ec ON e.campaign_id = ec.email_id GROUP BY e.campaign_name ORDER BY total_clicks DESC
SELECT es.email_address, COUNT(ec.email_id) AS total_clicks FROM EmailSubscribers es JOIN EmailClicks ec ON es.subscriber_id = ec.subscriber_id GROUP BY es.email_address ORDER BY total_clicks DESC

SELECT ec.click_date, es.email_address, ecc.engagement_type FROM EmailClicks ec JOIN EmailSubscribers es ON ec.subscriber_id = es.subscriber_id JOIN EmailEngagement ecc ON ec.subscriber_id = ecc.subscriber_id ORDER BY ec.click_date DESC
